						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Parakēsarivarman Parāntaka I, 4th year = A.D. 911.</p>						

						<p>Gift of a dish, a trumpet, a hanging lamp, a bell and an image to the temple by a <hi rend="italic">chōḻiya-vāṇiyaṉ</hi> called Muṇḍan Araṅgaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Nārpatteṇṇāyira-panmāhēśvara-Māyilaṭṭi. The stone with the inscription was also his gift.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIX, No. 99.]</p>						

